16 A Joint Resolution directing the Secretary of State
to refer to the people for their approval or
17 rejection a proposed amendment to Section 1 of
Article VII of the Oklahoma Constitution; prohibiting
18 courts and the state or political subdivisions from
recognizing and enforcing certain codes or laws;
19 updating language; providing ballot title; and
directing filing.
20
21
22 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES AND THE SENATE OF THE
23 2ND SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE:
24
ENGR. H. J. R. NO. 1084 Page 1

1 SECTION 1. The Secretary of State shall refer to the people for
2 their approval or rejection, as and in the manner provided by law,
3 the following proposed amendment to Section 1 of Article VII of the
4 Oklahoma Constitution to read as follows:
5 Section 1. A. The judicial power of this State shall be vested
6 in the Senate, sitting as a Court of Impeachment, a Supreme Court,
7 the Court of Criminal Appeals, the Court on the Judiciary, the State
8 Industrial Court, the Court of Bank Review, the Court of Tax Review,
9 and such intermediate appellate courts as may be provided by
10 statute, District Courts, and such Boards, Agencies and Commissions
11 created by the Constitution or established by statute as exercise
12 adjudicative authority or render decisions in individual
13 proceedings. Provided that the Court of Criminal Appeals, the State
14 Industrial Court, the Court of Bank Review and the Court of Tax
15 Review and such Boards, Agencies and Commissions as have been
16 established by statute shall continue in effect, subject to the
17 power of the Legislature to change or abolish said such Courts,
18 Boards, Agencies, or Commissions. Municipal Courts in cities or
19 incorporated towns shall continue in effect and shall be subject to
20 creation, abolition or alteration by the Legislature by general
21 laws, but shall be limited in jurisdiction to criminal and traffic
22 proceedings arising out of infractions of the provisions of
23 ordinances of cities and towns or of duly adopted regulations
24 authorized by such ordinances.
ENGR. H. J. R. NO. 1084 Page 2

1 B. No court, the state, or any political subdivision, board,
2 agency, or commission created by the Constitution or established by
3 statute shall recognize or enforce any religious code, body of law,
4 or practice that is repugnant to, incompatible with, or that does
5 not recognize and protect the same or equivalent individual rights
6 and liberties guaranteed under the Constitution of the State of
7 Oklahoma or the Constitution of the United States of America.
8 SECTION 2. The Ballot Title for the proposed Constitutional
9 amendment as set forth in SECTION 1 of this resolution shall be in
10 the following form:
11 BALLOT TITLE
12 Legislative Referendum No. ____ State Question No. ____
13 THE GIST OF THE PROPOSITION IS AS FOLLOWS:
14 This measure amends Section 1 of Article 7 of the Constitution.
15 It prohibits a court, the state, or any political subdivision
16 from recognizing or enforcing any religious code, law, or
17 practice that is in opposition to the Constitutions of Oklahoma
18 or the United States of America.
19 SHALL THE PROPOSAL BE APPROVED?
20 FOR THE PROPOSAL — YES _____________
21 AGAINST THE PROPOSAL — NO _____________
22 SECTION 3. The Chief Clerk of the House of Representatives,
23 immediately after the passage of this resolution, shall prepare and
24 file one copy thereof, including the Ballot Title set forth in
ENGR. H. J. R. NO. 1084 Page 3

1 SECT ION 2 hereof, with the Secretary of State and one copy with the
2 Attorney General.
3 Passed the House of Representatives the 24th day of March, 2026.
